🌦️ Weather Automation Tool (V2)
📖 Project Overview
The Weather Automation Tool (V2) is a Python-based application that automates the process of fetching real-time weather data for any city using the OpenWeatherMap API.
This version improves on V1 by integrating live API data, adding input handling, and displaying a clear, formatted weather report.
⚙️ Features
✅ Fetches real-time weather data from OpenWeatherMap
✅ Displays temperature, humidity, weather description, and wind speed
✅ Accepts user input for city name
✅ Simple, clean command-line interface (CLI)
✅ Handles invalid city names and API errors gracefully
🧰 Technologies Used
Python 3
Requests Library (for API calls)
OpenWeatherMap API
